{
  "stem": "19923.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 73.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that's the type of lifestyle we had, being-- not being able to mingle with the Germans, having people throw stones at you, not being allowed to go to public parks.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were not allowed to eventually go into German stores.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had to go to Jewish stores.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So my earliest recollection in Germany, when I was six and seven, was that it became very intolerable for Jewish people to live in Germany.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I knew that my-- some of my relatives were already making plans to leave.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My father had a first cousin who left and came to New York in 1937.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Later on in life I saw him, Max Newman.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He lived in-- he lived in-- in New York with his family.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was my father's first cousin.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In fact, he's the only member of my father's family that I ever knew, that first cousin Max Newman, and he lived in Brooklyn.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he was a waiter in Brooklyn, and he worked in the-- in the same bar as a waiter all his life.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And in the '40s when I went to New York, I used to visit him once in a while.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So yes, there was one member of my father's family that I knew.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Now, Germans-- the Jewish people who could were getting out of there.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My father, of course, didn't have the financial ability and didn't know-- didn't have any contacts that he knew of in-- in New York, although on my mother's side there were.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So he never made any attempts, as far as I know, to leave Germany.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But the-- I do recollect, earlier in my life, a period of time when there was no antisemitism in Cologne.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
